nodes.title: USER_GUIDE
widgets_values:
With WilcardMode enable
1-. Enter the text prompt using the categoy name __Category__ to indicate the field that should be replace by values from the wildcards.yaml or .json file
2. Use __Category/*__ to select rendom value from the item list use __Category/**__ to select the random value from within the subdirectories
3. Enter the dynamic_prompt select the variable name for the category then enter the equal simbol= and the values between curly brackets{} values separated by pipes| Color={red|blue|white|black} the script will create a prompt for each values overriding the values contained on the wildcards yaml or json file for the specific categories variables
4. select the maximun variant prompts you need with max_variants counter connect the text_list to a display text node
5. Execute the node
__Prefix__ a woman wearing a __Colors/**__ __Clothing/**__ enjoying a delicious __Food__  photograph by __Artist__

Prefix={close-up, dramatic lighting, intense gaze into camera|full-body shot, dynamic pose, slightly tilted angle}}
Food={a pizza|a cup of wine|a cup of coffe}}

# Initialize the canvas
canvas = Canvas()

# Set a global description for the canvas
canvas.set_global_description(
    description='A sorceress in a flowing purple gown conjures magic at the entrance of an ornate stone building.',
    detailed_descriptions=[
        'The scene depicts a mystical moment where a sorceress dressed in a flowing purple gown is casting spells at the entrance of an ornate stone building.',
        'She stands confidently, her robes billowing as she gestures with one hand while holding a glowing orb in the other.',
        'The entrance to the building is adorned with intricate carvings and elaborate stonework, giving it a grandiose appearance.',
        "The sorceress's expression is intense and focused, her eyes glowing with magical energy.",
        'Light emanates from the magic she conjures, illuminating her figure and casting shadows on the stone facade of the building.',
        'The background includes ancient trees and cobblestone paths, adding to the enchanting atmosphere.',
    ],
    tags='sorceress, purple gown, magic, entrance, ornate stone building, carvings, stonework, grandiose, spells, glowing orb, intense expression, magical energy, light, shadows, ancient trees, cobblestone paths, enchantment, mystical, mystical moment',

)

# Add the sorceress in a flowing purple gown.
canvas.add_local_description(
    location='in the center',
    offset='no offset',
    area='a medium-sized square area',
    distance_to_viewer=2.0,
    description='The sorceress in a flowing purple gown.',
    detailed_descriptions=[
        'The sorceress stands confidently in the center, her purple gown flowing gracefully around her.',
        'Her attire is intricate, with shimmering threads and delicate embroidery that match the magical aura she exudes.',
        "She's mid-spell, with one hand raised high above her head and the other holding a glowing orb.",
        'Her eyes are closed in concentration as magical energy crackles around her hands.',

    tags='sorceress, purple gown, magic, spellcasting, confidence, intricate attire, shimmering threads, embroidery, magical aura',

    HTML_web_color_name='mediumpurple',
)

# Add an ornate stone building entrance.

    location='on the right',

    area='a medium-sized vertical area',
    distance_to_viewer=3.5,
    description='An ornate stone building entrance.',
    detailed_descriptions=[
        'The entrance of the building is grand and imposing, with tall arches and intricate carvings covering its stonework.',
        'Elaborate designs in the form of mythical creatures and ancient runes adorn the pillars and walls.',
        "The structure's facade reflects light from the sorceress's magic, creating a dramatic play of shadows.",
    ],
    tags='ornate stone building, entrance, arches, carvings, stonework, grand, imposing, mythical creatures, ancient runes',
    atmosphere="A sense of ancient power and history emanates from the building's facade.",
    style='Architectural illustration with a focus on intricate details and light play.',
    quality_meta='Highly detailed architectural elements with dramatic lighting effects.',
    HTML_web_color_name='slategray',
)

# Add ancient trees adding to the enchanted atmosphere.
canvas.add_local_description(
    location='on the left',
    offset='no offset',
    area='a small vertical area',
    distance_to_viewer=4.0,
    description='Ancient trees adding to the enchanted atmosphere.',
    detailed_descriptions=[
        'The background features ancient, gnarled trees that add to the mystical ambiance of the scene.',
        "Their branches twist and curl, with leaves shimmering in shades of green and gold.",
        'These trees stand tall against a backdrop of blue sky, their roots stretching out over cobblestone paths that wind through the forest.',
    ],
    tags='ancient trees, gnarled, mystical ambiance, branches, leaves, green, gold, blue sky, roots, cobblestone paths',
    atmosphere='A serene yet magical ambiance created by the presence of ancient trees.',
    style="Nature illustration with an emphasis on texture and light to enhance the scene's enchantment.",
    quality_meta='Detailed portrayal of natural elements that contribute to the overall mystique of the setting.',
    HTML_web_color_name='forestgreen',
)

# Add cobblestone paths winding through the forest.
canvas.add_local_description(
    location='on the bottom-left',
    offset='slightly to the upper-right',
    area='a small horizontal area',
    distance_to_viewer=5.0,
    description='Cobblestone paths winding through the forest.',
    detailed_descriptions=[
        'The ground is covered with cobblestones that lead the eye deeper into the scene.',
        "These stones are worn and uneven, showing signs of age that match the building's grandeur.",
        'The path winds its way through the ancient trees, inviting viewers to explore further and adding a sense of depth to the overall composition.',
    ],
    tags='cobblestone paths, forest, stone, worn, uneven, age, grandeur, winding',
    atmosphere="A path that leads the viewer's eye deeper into the enchanted forest.",
    style='Textural detail in the cobblestones enhances the sense of realism and depth.',
    quality_meta='High-quality textures on the stones create a visually engaging pathway through the scene.',
    HTML_web_color_name='dimgray',
)

# Add magical light emanating from the sorceress's spell.
canvas.add_local_description(
    location='on the top-right',
    offset='no offset',
    area='a small square area',
    distance_to_viewer=6.0,
    description="Magical light emanating from the sorceress's spell.",
    detailed_descriptions=[
        "The spellcasting of the sorceress causes magical energy to illuminate the scene, casting a radiant glow across her and the surrounding environment.",
        'This light is both warm and otherworldly, adding an ethereal quality to the overall image.',
        'Shadows created by this illumination enhance the dramatic effect, creating a striking contrast against the stone building and trees.',

    tags='magical light, spellcasting, illumination, radiant glow, ethereal, warmth, contrast, shadows',

    style='Ethereal lighting techniques to create an enchanting visual effect.',

)

nodes.title: load images S
widgets_values:
The load images s has a quirk where you need to make sure the start index is not hihgher than the max amounts of images of the imported folder or the stop index 
Is logic but easy to forget lol

Don't use the upload button

select folder make sure to copy the address from the search bar and paste it into the pop up or directly into the input path hit refresh select your range of images to work with if the images are too large the api won't recognise it so you either resize them manualy or use the resizer node before feeding them to IF_LLM
If the images aren't too important you can use the backup button on the node otherwise I recommend saving your work before you start using this.

nodes.title: LLM node
widgets_values:
MAKE SURE to select the right provider and model, when this first load the model might not be for the same provider youi have selected and it fails

Some providers won't accept images or won't take the images into account
you need to chose vision compatible models to use images

You can use transformers QwenVL for local or any of the other local providers such as ollama

For online APIs you need to create either sytem 
Enviroment variables or place the variables on the custom node .env file

the names must the same as the providers list but in CAPITALS and adding _API_KEY

DEEPSEEK_API_KEY  
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
GROQ_API_KEY
HUGGINFACE_API_KEY (Not Yet available ComingUp)
MISTRAL_API_KEY
OPENAI_API_KEY
GEMINI_API_KEY
XAI_API_KEY

create and edit only works with 
OpenAI API and dalle3 for now

omost strategy only works with a particular omost model 

ollama run impactframes/dolphin_llama3_omost 

to install it
You can use native comfy load image if you are not interested in processing a list or batch
